summary: You know how some of the hero names are kind of more internal designations than they are Official Hero Names? (Like, how...
question: You know how some of the hero names are kind of more internal designations than they are Official Hero Names? (Like, how ‘Hawkeye’ is more a SHIELD code name that morphed into a hero name.) Now I kind of want ‘Captain Marvel’ to be a code name Fury put into the system as an inside joke to the pronunciation thing and it just sticks. Carol’s like ‘wait what’.
answer: That would be hilarious and I love it but I also love the idea of Carol choosing it to honor Mar-vell like she did in the comics. However I feel like she would have fought Fury on the pronunciation like she did at the end of CM. So maybe we can have it both ways, like she chose it but with the correct pronunciation but then when she comes back, she’s like YOU PUT IT IN AS MARVEL LIKE THE MARVELETTES FURY?! REALLY?! I TOLD YOU!
